n'''Sveti Toma\u017e''' ({{IPA-sl|\u02c8s\u028be\u02d0ti t\u0254\u02c8ma\u02d0\u0283|pron}}; {{lang-de|Sankt Thomas}}<ref name=\"Leksikon\">''Leksikon ob\u010din kraljestev in de\u017eel zastopanih v dr\u017eavnem zboru,'' vol. 6: ''Kranjsko''. 1906. Vienna: C. Kr. Dvorna in Dr\u017eavna Tiskarna, p. 62.</ref>) is a small settlement in the [[Municipality of \u0160kofja Loka]] in the [[Upper Carniola]] region of [[Slovenia]].\n\n==Name==\nThe name of the settlement was changed from ''Sveti Toma\u017e'' (literally, 'Saint Thomas') to ''Toma\u017e nad Praprotnim'' (literally, 'Thomas above Praprotno') in 1955. The name was changed on the basis of the 1948 Law on Names of Settlements and Designations of Squares, Streets, and Buildings as part of efforts by Slovenia's postwar communist government to remove religious elements from toponyms.<ref>''Spremembe naselij 1948\u201395''. 1996. Database. Ljubljana: Geografski in\u0161titut ZRC SAZU, DZS.</ref><ref>Premk, F. 2004. Slovenska versko-kr\u0161\u010danska terminologija v zemljepisnih imenih in spremembe za \u010das 1921\u20131967/68. ''Besedoslovne lastnosti slovenskega jezika: slovenska zemljepisna imena''. Ljubljana: Slavisti\u010dno dru\u0161tvo Slovenije, pp. 113\u2013132.</ref><ref>Urbanc, Mimi, & Matej Gabrovec. 2005. Krajevna imena: poligon za dokazovanje mo\u010di in odraz lokalne identitete. ''Geografski vestnik'' 77(2): 25\u201343.</ref> The name ''Sveti Toma\u017e'' was restored in 2000.<ref>[http://www.stat.si/krajevnaimena/default.asp?txtIme=TOMA%8E&selNacin=kjerkoli&selTip=naselja&ID=4398 Statistical Office of the Republic of Slovenia: Sv. Toma\u017e]</ref> In the past the German name was ''Sankt Thomas''.<ref name=\"Leksikon\"/>\n\n==Church==\n[[File:Sveti Tomaz Skofja Loka Slovenia - church.jpg|thumb|left|Saint Thomas's Church]]\nThe original church in the settlement, dedicated to [[Thomas the Apostle|Saint Thomas]], was a [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] structure with a square [[nave]] and a rounded [[apse]]. The remains of this are still visible in the corner of the [[sanctuary]]. The surviving sanctuary is mostly [[Gothic architecture|Gothic]], dating to around 1500. The church was rebuilt a number of times, most extensively in 1848 when three layers of [[fresco]]s were revealed, the oldest dating to the early 14th century, the second layer to around 1400, and the top layer to the early 16th century.<ref>[http://apl.e-soft.si/doc/5808/OS%20gradivo-18cerkva.pdf \u0160kofja Loka municipal declaration of local churches as cultural monuments, 23 May 2007] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110811144546/http://apl.e-soft.si/doc/5808/OS%20gradivo-18cerkva.pdf |date=11 August 2011 }}</ref>\n{{clear left}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.geopedia.si/Geopedia_en.html#L410_F10137934_T13_b4_x442133.5_y116083.5_s15 Sveti Toma\u017e at Geopedia]\n*{{commons category-inline|Sveti Toma\u017e, \u0160kofja Loka}}\n\n{{\u0160kofja Loka}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sveti Tomaz, Skofja Loka}}\n[[Category:Populated places in the Municipality of \u0160kofja Loka]]\n\n\n{{\u0160kofjaLoka-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Sveti Toma\u017e\n|other_name             = Toma\u017e nad Praprotnim (1955\u20132000)\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               =\n|settlement_type        = <!--For Town or Village (Leave blank for the default City)-->\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = St. Thomas church on a winter morning.jpg\n|imagesize              = 250px\n|image_caption          =\n|image_flag             =\n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             =\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              =\n|mapsize          